---
id: org.dxos.plugin.thread
name: ThreadPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

ThreadPlugin provides chat: channels backed by an ECHO feed and free-standing message threads.
It renders the channel article + companion surfaces and a thread surface, and contributes the
operations that create a channel and append messages. Shared message/thread UI comes from
`@dxos/react-ui-thread`, and the `Channel`/`Message`/`Thread` schema comes from `@dxos/types`.
Document comments and the comment-thread AI agent live in `@dxos/plugin-comments`.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |

## Types

```mdl
type Channel
  desc: |
    A chat channel. Defined in @dxos/types. Carries an optional `feed` Ref whose
    queue holds the channel's Message objects in order.
```

## Operations

```mdl
op OnCreateSpace
  key: org.dxos.plugin.thread.operation.onCreateSpace
  desc: On space creation, create a default "General" channel in the root collection.
```

```mdl
op CreateChannel
  key: org.dxos.plugin.thread.operation.createChannel
  desc: Create a new Channel in the given space.
  in:
    spaceId: SpaceId
    name?: String
  out:
    object: Channel
```

```mdl
op AppendChannelMessage
  key: org.dxos.plugin.thread.operation.appendChannelMessage
  desc: Append a Message authored by `sender` to the channel's feed.
  in:
    channel: Channel
    sender: Actor
    text: String
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Channel chat
  req F-1.1: A Channel article MUST render its feed messages newest-last with a
    pinned composer; sending invokes AppendChannelMessage.
  req F-1.2: Externally-synced channels (those carrying foreign-key Obj.Meta) MUST
    render read-only — the composer is suppressed.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Thread chat
  req F-2.1: A Thread article MUST render the thread's messages and append new
    messages by pushing onto `thread.messages`.
```
